e, "type": "link", "uuid": "1ASZaW238B", "is_twitter": true, "is_admin": false, "score": 55, "suggested_sort": 0, "post_flair_class": "", "id": 8588857, "raw_content": "", "author": "Eruditio", "created": 1777466826437, "profile_picture": "", "community": "TheDonald", "ad_tier": 2, "last_comment_author": "clownworld30330", "is_video": false, "video_link": "", "is_new_user": false, "domain": "twitter.com", "is_crosspost": false, "preview": "https://media.scored.co/preview/1ASZaW238B.png", "removal_source": "", "link": "https://twitter.com/RepBrandonGill/status/2049160492438917349", "author_flair_class": "", "is_removed": false, "media": {"resized_resolutions": [], "blurhash": "", "full_resolution": []}, "title": "Rep. Brandon Gill Flusters Abortion Advocate By Asking What Her \u2018Favorite Method\u2019 Is", "last_comment_created": 1777473380301, "content": "", "score_down": 0, "author_flair_text": "", "pro_tier": 0, "is_stickied": false, "is_nsfw": false, "is_deleted": false, "is_image": false, "comments": 2, "score_up": 55, "is_edited": false, "is_moderator": false, "awards": 0, "vote_state": 2, "link_metadata": {"twitter": {"quotedTweet": false, "images": false, "linkEmbed": false, "replies": 6088, "created": 1777392907000, "id": "2049160492438917349", "video": {"preview": "https://pbs.twimg.com/amplify_video_thumb/2049160317608071168/img/Q2jP60eabuaSwipH.jpg", "mpeg": "https://video.twimg.com/amplify_video/2049160317608071168/pl/ZmDX1WGqVSvvrQIn.m3u8?v=058", "aspectRatio": [1, 1], "heightRatio": 100, "type": "video/mp4", "url": "https://video.twimg.com/amplify_video/2049160317608071168/vid/avc1/320x320/hjG7_CW3fcp1O4TP.mp4"}, "poll": false, "user": {"profilePicture": "https://pbs.twimg.com/profile_images/1864016375850659840/GkXxhrzb_normal.jpg", "displayName": "Congressman Brandon Gill", "username": "RepBrandonGill"}, "content": "Today I asked an abortion advocate what her favorite method of abortion is.", "parentTweet": false, "likes": 101201}}, "post_flair_text": "", "archive_id": ""}, {"is_locked": false, "tweet_id": "", "sticky_comment": 0, "is_video_mp4": false, "type": "text", "uuid": "1ASZaX8WAq", "is_twitter": false, "is_admin": false, "score": 33, "suggested_sort": 0, "post_flair_class": "", "id": 8589130, "raw_content": "Babylon was more than a city. It was a symbol of human pride turned into a system. In the story of Babel, mankind tries to build upward toward heaven, not just with stone, but with ambition. It is the dream that human unity, planning, and power can replace God, tradition, and natural order.\n\nModern globalism is our new Babel. It promises peace through centralization, prosperity through managed markets, and unity through the weakening of nations, cultures, and inherited identities. It imagines that the world can be perfected by institutions, treaties, technology, finance, and expert control.\n\nThe problem is not cooperation between nations. The problem is an ideology that treats rooted identity as dangerous, sovereignty as outdated, and tradition as an obstacle. As power moves farther from families, communities, and nations, accountability disappears. Citizens become managed populations. Culture becomes branding. Truth becomes policy. Freedom becomes permission.\n\nBabylon fell because it trusted its wealth, walls, priesthoods, and imperial order more than justice and humility. A global Babel faces the same danger. Its systems look advanced, but they are fragile because they are built on abstraction rather than belonging.\n\nIf we continue down this path, our fate may resemble Babylon\u2019s. The collapse may not come through conquest, but through confusion, distrust, spiritual exhaustion, and institutional decay. Babel falls when imposed unity can no longer hide the disorder underneath. A civilization that replaces truth with administration eventually loses the human foundation it needs to survive.\n", "author": "HeNotMedicated", "created": 1777476036654, "profile_picture": "", "community": "TheDonald", "ad_tier": 2, "last_comment_author": "liberpede", "is_video": false, "video_link": "", "is_new_user": false, "domain": "", "is_crosspost": false, "preview": "", "removal_source": "", "link": "", "author_flair_class": "", "is_removed": false, "media": {"resized_resolutions": [], "blurhash": "", "full_resolution": []}, "title": "The New Babel Is Already Falling", "last_comment_created": 1777482379582, "content": "<p>Babylon was more than a city. It was a symbol of human pride turned into a system. In the story of Babel, mankind tries to build upward toward heaven, not just with stone, but with ambition. It is the dream that human unity, planning, and power can replace God, tradition, and natural order.</p>\n<p>Modern globalism is our new Babel. It promises peace through centralization, prosperity through managed markets, and unity through the weakening of nations, cultures, and inherited identities. It imagines that the world can be perfected by institutions, treaties, technology, finance, and expert control.</p>\n<p>The problem is not cooperation between nations. The problem is an ideology that treats rooted identity as dangerous, sovereignty as outdated, and tradition as an obstacle. As power moves farther from families, communities, and nations, accountability disappears. Citizens become managed populations. Culture becomes branding. Truth becomes policy. Freedom becomes permission.</p>\n<p>Babylon fell because it trusted its wealth, walls, priesthoods, and imperial order more than justice and humility. A global Babel faces the same danger. Its systems look advanced, but they are fragile because they are built on abstraction rather than belonging.</p>\n<p>If we continue down this path, our fate may resemble Babylon\u2019s. The collapse may not come through conquest, but through confusion, distrust, spiritual exhaustion, and institutional decay. Babel falls when imposed unity can no longer hide the disorder underneath. A civilization that replaces truth with administration eventually loses the human foundation it needs to survive.</p>\n", "score_down": 0, "author_flair_text": "", "pro_tier": 0, "is_stickied": false, "is_nsfw": false, "is_deleted": false, "is_image": false, "comments": 7, "score_up": 33, "is_edited": false, "is_moderator": false, "awards": 0, "vote_state": 2, "link_metadata": {"status": 200}, "post_flair_text": "", "archive_id": ""}, {"is_locked": false, "tweet_id": "", "sticky_comment": 0, "is_video_mp4": false, "type": "link", "uuid": "1ASZaX8WF7", "is_twitter": false, "is_admin": false, "score": 32, "suggested_sort": 0, "post_flair_class": "", "id": 8589149, "raw_content": "", "author": "TateDemarcus", "created": 1777476531211, "profile_picture": "", "community": "TheDonald", "ad_tier": 2, "last_comment_author": "Formerlurker92", "is_video": false, "video_link": "", "is_new_user": false, "domain": "cdn.5mind.com", "is_crosspost": false, "preview": "https://media.scored.co/preview/1ASZaX8WF7.png", "removal_source": "", "link": "https://cdn.5mind.com/uploads/production/Xp9Mac5LPGEVHPRCUM0m0/image/CjC_Pv0aNw7hnvu_KLGnX.jpeg", "author_flair_class": "", "is_removed": false, "media": {"resized_resolutions": [{"reference": "/scale/jOt3oEZky8ivMKO5.jpeg", "width": 645, "content-type": "jpeg", "height": 768}], "blurhash": "UFG*Tm0NKiTK~BIVX8kWJ6s8R+W._MIa$+t7", "full_resolution": [1283, 1078]}, "title": "What make us human... \ud83d\ude02", "last_comment_created": 1777482117828, "content": "", "score_down": 0, "author_flair_text": "", "pro_tier": 0, "is_stickied": false, "is_nsfw": false, "is_deleted": false, "is_image": true, "comments": 4, "score_up": 32, "is_edited": false, "is_moderator": false, "awards": 0, "vote_state": 2, "link_metadata": {"status": 200}, "post_flair_text": "", "archive_id": ""}, {"is_locked": false, "tweet_id": "2049276475741004177", "sticky_comment": 0, "is_video_mp4": false, "type": "link", "uuid": "1ASZaX8F3h", "is_twitter": true, "is_admin": false, "score": 40, "suggested_sort":